But in spite of a wind - driven rainstorm , gridlock never materialized , mainly because <COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">the Bay Area Rapid Transit subway system</COREF> carried 50 % more passengers than normal .
For the first time in memory , it was standing - room only in <COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">BART 's</COREF> sleek , modern railcars .
Moreover , the two main bridges still connecting <COREF ID="11" TYPE="IDENT">San Francisco</COREF> with <COREF ID="7" TYPE="IDENT">the East Bay</COREF> did n't charge tolls , allowing traffic to zip through without stopping .
Officials also suspect that traffic benefited from steps by major employers to get workers to come in at odd hours , or that many workers are still staying at home .
